The media could not be loaded.
 Beautiful and no taste ! When the glitter settles to the bottom, just swirl the drink with a spoon or a straw and the magic starts again ! A little goes a LONG way. More glitter gives you a shimmery swirl effect in the drink while less glitter just gives a beautiful floating sparkle effect.

I just wish Prime would cover all colors. I SO wanted to get the blue iridescent and the rose gold, but the shipping isn't cheap since the company is U.S. based (if I'm not mistaking).

Anyway, very happy with my purchase ! Would buy again !

Becca's mama
5.0 out of 5 stars Lasts So Long!!!
Reviewed in the United States on August 18, 2022
Colour Name: SilverVerified Purchase
The media could not be loaded.
 10/10 easily!! The product has no flavor which means it can be added to any beverage. The glitter only shows up in clear drinks, but you can still use some of the colors to dye things like milk. The iridescent is gorgeous but very subtle, I'd suggest using it in a well lit area (you can mix in glitter for a really beautiful effect.) The glitters are very pigmented and they release a little bit more color into your drink after a few minutes so you don't have to add a lot at all. I typically pour the glitter into the cap (very small amount, maybe a fingernail sized portion) and I can easily control the amount I put in to avoid accidentally dumping too much. Overall, I have gotten so many compliments on drinks I've used this in and I love it too. It can even help you be healthier if you always go for soda or if you aren't hydrated enough because if you're anything like me you will have water more frequently just to see the pretty effect the glitter provides. I love this product so much. I have 4 colors right now and I carry them with me everywhere just in case. I just ordered another and I have a list of more colors that I want in the future. (Pro tip #1: If you do want a dark soda you can add the silver glitter. It has no impact on the color but you can see the glitter when the drink is mixed.) (Pro tip #2: Due to how fine the glitter is I'd recommend opening and closing the jar under the table if you're at a restaurant. The iridescent glitters have a slightly different formula that sticks to itself more so you don't have to do this for those glitters.) (Pro tip #3, if you want to get the best effect while drinking a cold drink I recommend wiping away any cloudy condensation on the outside of the glass as it can obstruct the view of the glitter.) (Pro tip #4: While any coloring the glitter provides will stay distributed, the glitter itself does sink after a few minutes. I recommend using a straw when drinking this so that you can mix it a little before every sip and make your drink look gorgeous the whole night. If you're like me, in addition to carrying the glitter at all times you can carry an eco-friendly straw so that you don't create too much pollution every time you use this product. ^-^)
